main event: An Air Force officer reported observing a UFO near Fort Huachuca, Arizona, on February 23, 1963.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes., The object was observed visually moving from east to west., The conclusion of the sighting was that the object was a balloon., The officer reported no physical evidence or photographs were taken., Weather conditions included approximately 39% thin cloud cover at the time of the sighting.
witness description: USAF officer, electronics technician, excellent reliability
